revision.text:
'''William "Bill" Larsen, Jr.''' (May 8, 1928 – February 11, 1993)<ref>{{cite news |title=Bill Larsen Jr. |work=[[Genii (magazine)|Genii]] |date=April 1993 |page=363}}</ref> was a famous [[Illusionist|magician]] who usually teamed up with his brother, [[Milt Larsen]]. Along with Milt, he has a star on the [[Hollywood Walk of Fame]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Milt & Bill Larsen - Hollywood Star Walk |url=http://projects.latimes.com/hollywood/star-walk/milt-bill-larsen/ |accessdate=August 10, 2016 |author=Cecilia Rasmussen |work=The Los Angeles Times |date=February 9, 2003}}</ref> He and his brother and wife, [[Irene Larsen]], were co-founders of the [[Magic Castle]] and the Academy of Magical Arts.

